Key Match Events: Jake Bauers hit a walk-off single in the ninth inning to lift the Milwaukee Brewers over the Philadelphia Phillies 2-1.
Rhys Hoskins hit his 25th home run, tying the game in the fifth inning.
Pre-Game Insights: The Brewers had clinched the NL Central earlier in the day, but needed to win this game to prevent the Phillies from securing a playoff berth.
Philadelphia manager Rob Thomson said 'Two really good teams, low scoring, tight games. Those are the games you certainly like to win and hate to lose.'
Post-Match Reflections: Bauers said 'I think the vibe in the clubhouse all day was, that's great that we (clinched), but we need to win this game.'
Adames said 'Everybody was doubting us at the beginning, that we were going to be able to do this. We proved them wrong. Hopefully we can go all the way and win it all.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Phillies' magic number to qualify for the playoffs is one, and four to clinch the NL East.
The Brewers are 88-64 with 10 games to go as they chase the Phillies and Dodgers for the National League's two first-round playoff byes.
